<div><div><h2>Founders of Panama Papers Law Firm Arrested on Money Laundering Charges</h2></div><div>police in panama arrested the founders of mossack fonseca the law firm at the center of the panama papers scandal on money laundering charges thursday after authorities raided the firm\xe2\x80\x99s headquarters as part of investigations into brazil\xe2\x80\x99s largest-ever bribery scandal. police in panama arrested the founders of mossack fonseca the law firm at the center of the panama papers scandal on money laundering charges after authorities raided the firm\xe2\x80\x99s headquarters as part of investigations into brazil\xe2\x80\x99s largest-ever bribery scandal. the firm\xe2\x80\x99s founding partners ram\xc3\xb3n fonseca and j\xc3\xbcrgen mossack were taken into police custody on thursday according to the men\xe2\x80\x99s lawyer. kenia porcell panama\xe2\x80\x99s attorney general <a href="http://ministeriopublico.gob.pa/comunicado-12/">released a statement</a> that said evidence gathered by her office indicated that the law firm was a potential \xe2\x80\x9ccriminal organization\xe2\x80\x9d that concealed and removed evidence related to \xe2\x80\x9cillegal activity.\xe2\x80\x9d both fonseca and mossack are <a href="https://panamapapers.icij.org/20160403-mossack-fonseca-offshore-secrets.html">well-known in business and political circles</a> in panama. fonseca is a former adviser to panama\xe2\x80\x99s president juan varela and mossack served on panama\xe2\x80\x99s council on foreign relations from 2009 to 2014. they have consistently denied any wrongdoing. their law firm says that it is not at fault in cases in which offshore companies it set up for clients were later used for illegitimate purposes. the firm told icij last year that it follows \xe2\x80\x9cboth the letter and spirit of the law.\xe2\x80\x9d mossack fonseca issued a statement thursday that <a href="http://mossfonmedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/mf-february-raid.pdf">accused</a> panamanian officials of \xe2\x80\x9can attempt to divert the attention from those who really merit a deep and proactive investigation.\xe2\x80\x9d it said authorities \xe2\x80\x9chave not presented a single piece of evidence that shows us guilty.\xe2\x80\x9d the arrests come 10 months after the panama papers investigation by icij and other media partners revealed that mossack fonseca had set up or managed offshore companies and other hard-to-trace corporate structures for world leaders drug kingpins american fraudsters and other clients. icij german daily s\xc3\xbcddeutsche zeitung and more than 100 other media partners worked together to investigate a trove of 11.5 million leaked documents detailing the law firm\xe2\x80\x99s day-to-day operations over nearly 40 years. shortly before the media partnership began releasing its findings brazilian and panamanian authorities began targeting mossack fonseca as part of a wide-ranging bribery investigation in brazil \xe2\x80\x93 dubbed lava jato (\xe2\x80\x9coperation car wash\xe2\x80\x9d) \xe2\x80\x93 that has led to criminal charges against leading brazilian politicians. brazilian prosecutors said in january 2016 that they were investigating the law firm\xe2\x80\x99s alleged role in helping individuals involved in the multi-million-dollar bribery case use offshore companies to launder money. porcell panama\xe2\x80\x99s attorney general said in her statement that bribe money circulated through various companies and was then \xe2\x80\x9claundered or washed through panama.\xe2\x80\x9d the business dealings of odebrecht a brazil-based construction conglomerate has been a focus of the lava jato investigation. in december <a href="https://www.justice.gov/opa/pr/odebrecht-and-braskem-plead-guilty-and-agree-pay-least-35-billion-global-penalties-resolve">odebrecht pleaded guilty</a> in the united states and reached settlements with authorities in switzerland and brazil over allegations that it paid millions of dollars in bribes to government officials on three continents. after thursday\xe2\x80\x99s surprise raid ram\xc3\xb3n fonseca lashed out at president varela <a href="http://www.dw.com/en/panamas-president-varela-accused-of-accepting-odebrecht-donations/a-37489450">telling reporters</a> that varela had told him the president had accepted money from odebrecht the brazilian construction company \xe2\x80\x9cbecause he couldn\xe2\x80\x99t fight everyone.\xe2\x80\x9d varela <a href="https://www.presidencia.gob.pa/noticias/pronunciamiento-del-presidente-juan-carlos-varela">said</a> the contributions were donations not bribes. despite official statements that thursday\xe2\x80\x99s raid and detentions were related to brazil\xe2\x80\x99s lava jato case mossack fonseca\xe2\x80\x99s twitter account posted an image of a search warrant from the attorney general\xe2\x80\x99s office that referred to \xe2\x80\x9ca criminal investigation into alleged economic crimes in particular money laundering that has its origins in the journalistic investigation \xe2\x80\x98panama papers.\xe2\x80\x99\xe2\x80\x9d \xe2\x80\x94 mossack fonseca (@mossfon) <a href="https://twitter.com/mossfon/status/829850640654413824">february 10 2017</a> <script async="" src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8" type="text/javascript"></script></div><p>\xe2\x80\x9cthe documents obtained by the international consortium of investigative journalists (icij) are related to the creation and sale of offshore companies by the panamanian law firm mossack fonseca\xe2\x80\x9d the document from the attorney general\xe2\x80\x99s office said. the companies were \xe2\x80\x9callegedly used for laundering millions of dollars from multiple illicit activities around the world.\xe2\x80\x9d \xe2\x80\x9clava jato case \xe2\x80\x9d mossack fonseca tweeted. \xe2\x80\x9chere is a search warrant indicating that it is #panamapapers.\xe2\x80\x9d \xe2\x80\x9cit\xe2\x80\x99s really confusing\xe2\x80\x9d guillermina macdonald mossack fonseca\xe2\x80\x99s lawyer told icij in a telephone interview friday afternoon. macdonald confirmed that mossack fonseca had received the official document that referred to the panama papers but said that when she visited the attorney general\xe2\x80\x99s office she was provided information related to lava jato. macdonald said she waited for four hours at the attorney general\xe2\x80\x99s office and was then denied access to complete documentation relating to charges relating to the firm. \xe2\x80\x9cthe attorney general\xe2\x80\x99s office doesn\xe2\x80\x99t show its face\xe2\x80\x9d she said. a spokeswoman for panama\xe2\x80\x99s attorney general told icij the arrests related to lava jato only. the raid comes during a busy month for mossack fonseca and related corruption and bribery scandals. this week ojo publico a peruvian news outlet that collaborated with icij on the panama papers investigation <a href="https://panamapapers.ojo-publico.com/articulo/operadores-de-toledo-tenian-red-de-offshore-operadas-por-mossack-fonseca/">reported</a> that mossack fonseca had created offshore companies for middlemen recently accused by peruvian authorities of helping to channel bribes to peru\xe2\x80\x99s former president alejandro toledo. toledo is currently under investigation in peru as part of a probe into $800 million in bribes paid across latin america by the odebrecht conglomerate. a judge in peru <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/judge-orders-arrest-of-former-peruvian-president-alejandro-toledo-in-odebrecht-bribery-case-1486698137">issued an arrest warrant</a> thursday for toledo citing a \xe2\x80\x9chigh degree of probability\xe2\x80\x9d that the former president took up to $20 million in bribes in exchange for awarding odebrecht public contracts during his time in office. separately mossack fonseca is in court <a href="http://mossfonmedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/statement-jan-25-2017.pdf">fighting panama\xe2\x80\x99s anti-corruption prosecutor</a> who was recently granted the power to indefinitely extend his investigation of the firm in relation to the panama papers.</div></div>